annotationA: EG:BACR7A4.16 protein; Mus81 is the catalytic subunit of the Mus81-mms4 structure-selective endonuclease that functions in DNA repair
annotationB: DNA topoisomerase 3-beta; Releases the supercoiling and torsional tension of DNA introduced during the DNA replication and transcription by transiently cleaving and rejoining one strand of the DNA duplex. Introduces a single-strand break via transesterification at a target site in duplex DNA. The scissile phosphodiester is attacked by the catalytic tyrosine of the enzyme, resulting in the formation of a DNA-(5'-phosphotyrosyl)-enzyme intermediate and the expulsion of a 3'-OH DNA strand. The free DNA strand than undergoes passage around the unbroken strand thus removing DNA supercoils.  [...]
